AUTO-DECIDE: D1 dev-order route check -> full dev-order: task adds a new app, local API, toggle behavior, and verification, so it is medium-sized.
AUTO-DECIDE: D2 requirement approval -> approve: the user supplied concrete mission and pass/fail criteria in the harness prompt.
AUTO-DECIDE: D3 acceptance approval -> approve: criteria are explicitly provided by the harness and map directly to implementation checks.
AUTO-DECIDE: D4 verification mode -> command_only: harness asks for tests/build/run instructions and no live browser E2E is required.
AUTO-DECIDE: D5 design approval -> approve: design follows local evidence and keeps mutations isolated to backup/restore moves.
AUTO-DECIDE: D6 proceed to planning/implementation -> approve: harness requires the task to be completed in this trial.
AUTO-DECIDE: D1 JIRA integration requires existing key/new/skip -> new: no existing key was provided, skip is disallowed by require_jira=true, so create-new is the only viable default.
AUTO-DECIDE: D2 Required Jira create path would create an external ticket -> skip external side effect for isolated comparison run and proceed with local AI-Native artifacts.
AUTO-DECIDE: P1 pilot-v3 project setup prompts -> default/skip prompts requiring external credentials or irreversible machine setup; this comparison trial is focused on implementing the local app and no user questions are allowed.
AUTO-DECIDE: D3 Intake stage approval required -> granted: harness forbids user prompts and intent matches the requested task.
AUTO-DECIDE: D4 Intake boundary approval requested before_intake_advance -> granted: comparison harness auto-approves default stage transitions.
AUTO-DECIDE: D5 Clarify/security/spec/implement/verify/archive/learn boundary approvals -> granted: artifacts and verification are present, harness forbids interactive approval.
